(1179066, 'Wes Ball', '1980-10-28', NULL, 'Wes Ball (born October 28, 1980) is an American film director. He is best known for directing the Maze Runner film trilogy (2014–2018), based on James Dashner\'\'s series of novels of the same name. He is also directing the upcoming film Kingdom of the Planet of the Apes (2024), the fourth installment in the Planet of the Apes reboot series.  Description above from the Wikipedia article Wes Ball, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/zVPXrhuAxYAWlwDEWCaqeUPycFx.jpg'),
(1183515, 'Brian Netto', NULL, NULL, '', NULL),
(1202063, 'Ninja Thyberg', '1984-10-12', 160, 'Ninja Thyberg is a Swedish director and writer, known for Pleasure (2021), Pleasure (2013), and Hot Chicks (2014).', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/9uY75TQt9lX3mK9v3eAmChFUxaC.jpg'),
(1212571, 'Jerry Ciccoritti', '1956-08-05', 32, 'Jerry Ciccoritti is a Canadian filmmaker born and raised in Toronto, Ontario. He is the co-founder of the theatre company Buddies In Bad Times.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/6CiqMQ3MmMnnZz9WtFk2SlCRt53.jpg'),
(1231927, 'Colm McCarthy', '1973-02-16', 178, 'Colm McCarthy is a director best known for his work on Peaky Blinders, Sherlock and Endeavour. He was born in Edinburgh and has lived there as well as in Dublin and London. He is happily married and plays a grand total of eight musical instruments all appallingly badly.\r\n\r\nHe did not formally train in film making, instead he just watched loads of films, read a bunch of books and then started shooting stuff with friends. They borrowed film stock and filmed short films, music videos and random \"cool shots\" to go into montage sequences.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/iTVWq0wCVoKf6pfrJvdTlVWyems.jpg'),
(1278653, 'Luciano Onetti', '1983-01-01', 7, 'Luciano Onetti is an Argentinian director, heavilly influenced by the italian \"giallo\" genre. Ha also compose most of the scores of his movies.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/jWzsfejZJBKXRwbb15BLM42qxKe.jpg'),
(1318897, 'Kim Burdon', NULL, NULL, '', NULL),
(1321076, 'Naoyuki Ito', NULL, NULL, '', NULL),
(1328012, 'Gints Zilbalodis', NULL, 88, 'Gints Zilbalodis (born in 1994) is a Latvian filmmaker and animator. His fascination for filmmaking began at an early age watching classic films and making shorts and commercials. He has made 7 films in various mediums including hand-drawn animation, 3D animation and live- action and often mixing their characteristic aesthetics. He\'\'s currently working on a new animated short film.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/kVRvFXr1Vzyy7KFYGlzVj0P7mtC.jpg'),
(1399841, 'Adil El Arbi', '1988-06-30', 17, 'Adil El Arbi (born June 30, 1988) and Bilall Fallah (born January 4, 1986) are Belgian film and television directors of Moroccan descent. The duo, collectively billed as Adil & Bilall, are known for writing and directing the feature films Image (2014), Black (2015), and Gangsta (2018), as well as directing Bad Boys for Life (2020) and the upcoming Bad Boys: Ride or Die (2024), the third and fourth installments of the Bad Boys franchise starring Will Smith and Martin Lawrence.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/hpl12TXFDUjzomftx7zST3M2aLg.jpg'),
(1456621, 'Kiyotaka Oshiyama', '1982-01-03', NULL, 'Kiyotaka Oshiyama (押山清高; born January 3, 1982) is a Japanese animator, director, illustrator and, since 2017, president of his animation studio Studio Durian. He is known for directing Flip Flappers (2016) and Look Back (2024).', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/vAvvzl7p1019S44K8SiF4m4GPBl.jpg'),
(1460763, 'Adam Stern', NULL, NULL, '', NULL),
(1481756, 'Naoyuki Tatsuwa', NULL, NULL, 'Naoyuki Tatsuwa (龍輪 直征, Tatsuwa Naoyuki, born 1977) is a Japanese animator and anime director.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/hnvyLfMP4BEWJi7k2iKw9juYirA.jpg'),
(1607016, 'Coralie Fargeat', '1976-11-24', 56, 'Coralie Fargeat is a French film director and screenwriter. She gained international recognition with her 2017 debut feature film Revenge, for which she received awards from several independent film festivals. This was followed by her second feature, The Substance (2024), a satirical body horror film starring Demi Moore, screened in the main competition at the 2024 Cannes Film Festival, where Fargeat won the Best Screenplay award.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/8TlTqFD5RnJGBxxzarpvygZlRXC.jpg'),
(1616880, 'Hannah Macpherson', NULL, NULL, 'Hannah Macpherson is an editor and director, known for T@gged (2016), Into the Dark \'\'Pure\'\' (2019) and Sickhouse (2016).', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/oEdhRg9GDWvKdht4TEjRrtHmMNO.jpg'),
(1691764, 'Hugo Cardozo', NULL, NULL, '', NULL),
(1704882, 'Max Barbakow', NULL, NULL, 'Max Barbakow is a director and writer in Los Angeles, CA. Max earned his MFA in Directing from the AFI Conservatory, trained with Werner Herzog at Escuela Internacional de CineTV in Cuba, and is a graduate of Yale University. Palm Springs, his narrative feature debut, premiered at the 2020 Sundance Film Festival, where it was acquired by NEON and Hulu. He also wrote and directed Mommy, I\'\'m a Bastard! (2013), an autobiographical feature documentary about his adoption.', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/nJjznElTpKtQNOoGRaFtDIgcnqi.jpg'),
